National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan and Afghan National Security Advisor Hamdullah Mohib had a conversation regarding the United States' engagement with Afghanistan as U.S. troops withdraw from the country. Sullivan emphasized the U.S.' commitment to the Afghan government and people, and both advisors reaffirmed the strength of the bilateral partnership. They also agreed to continue close consultation and outlined plans for ongoing security and civilian assistance to Afghanistan. The importance of the two governments working together towards common objectives, such as a negotiated political settlement to end the war, was stressed. Sullivan assured that the U.S. will support the Afghan people in their pursuit of lasting and inclusive peace.